data.body:
Although something like C:\path\Main.ext is the same thing as C:\path\main.ext for the Windows filesystem, Atom opens different windows. One with the title "Main.hx" and other with "main.hx"...
They point to the same file. If I edit and save one the other window is updated.

I'm using a tool that output the path always in lower case and atom.workspace.open to open in a given line and column.

On Windows 8.1, Atom 1.03, Javascript, the follow open two windows for the same file:

``` javascript
atom.workspace.open(path, {
  initialLine: line,
  initialColumn: column,
  searchAllPanes: true
});
```

``` javascript
atom.workspace.open(path.toLowerCase(), {
  initialLine: line,
  initialColumn: column,
  searchAllPanes: true
});
```

I want to change the selection color by using my user styles, I looked at how the "page" is built with the inspector and made various tests but none of them did anything, this is really frustrating...

What I tried:

``` less
.selection .region { background-color: red }
```

I thought maybe order was the issue so I tried:

``` less
.selection .region {
  border: 1px solid blue;
  background-color: blue !important;
}
```

When I look at the page source I see my styles added at the end in the header section, I see in its content what I added but if I inspect the ".selection .region" elements my style is not there.

I would be really glad if someone could guide me, I barely see the selection with my current theme and this is really annoying.
